âœ… Your Code is Perfect in Principle! But let's add these improvements:
1. Better Pointcut Naming (Avoid *.*(..))
This currently applies to all methods in the entire app including Springâ€™s internal ones, repositories, etc. ğŸ˜±
Let's scope it down.

@Pointcut("execution(* com.nathan.taskzen.service.*.*(..))")
public void allServiceMethods() {}
ğŸ¯ This limits AOP only to your service layer.

2. Improved Version of Your Aspect

@Aspect
@Component
public class LoggingAspect {

    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(LoggingAspect.class);

    @Pointcut("execution(* com.nathan.taskzen.service.*.*(..))")
    public void allServiceMethods() {}

    @Before("allServiceMethods()")
    public void logMethodCall(JoinPoint joinPoint) {
        LOGGER.info("â¡ï¸ Calling Method: {}", joinPoint.getSignature().toShortString());
    }

    @After("allServiceMethods()")
    public void logMethodExecuted(JoinPoint joinPoint) {
        LOGGER.info("âœ… Method Completed: {}", joinPoint.getSignature().toShortString());
    }

    @AfterReturning("allServiceMethods()")
    public void logMethodSuccess(JoinPoint joinPoint) {
        LOGGER.info("ğŸ‰ Method Succeeded: {}", joinPoint.getSignature().toShortString());
    }

    @AfterThrowing("allServiceMethods()")
    public void logMethodCrash(JoinPoint joinPoint) {
        LOGGER.error("ğŸ’¥ Method Failed: {}", joinPoint.getSignature().toShortString());
    }
}
3. ğŸ’¡ Enhance It More?
If you want to log input arguments, you can enhance like this:

@Around("allServiceMethods()")
public Object logExecutionTime(ProceedingJoinPoint pjp) throws Throwable {
    long start = System.currentTimeMillis();
    LOGGER.info("ğŸ“¥ Args: {}", Arrays.toString(pjp.getArgs()));

    Object result = pjp.proceed();

    long duration = System.currentTimeMillis() - start;
    LOGGER.info("â±ï¸ Execution Time: {} ms", duration);
    LOGGER.info("ğŸ“¤ Result: {}", result);

    return result;
}
ğŸ¯ Summary
Advice Type	Purpose
@Before	Log entry into method
@After	Run always after method
@AfterReturning	Only on success
@AfterThrowing	Only on exception
@Around	Surround full execution

